column36:
Likely a trigger post! *** #ButNotMaternity

Before I begin, I must clarify that this post does NOT include a very small percentage of women that have genuine complications and underline health issues. This applies to healthy women who have a mind of their own.

C-Sections for breech babies, induction for being 'overdue' inductions for 'big babies' hospital births for high BMI, hospital births for first time mums. All of the above are considered "high risk" to name just a few. While I could site evidence against all these points and more (feel free to ask, and I will gladly provide) my main point is; For the love of God ladies!!! Take your power and don't blindly follow these guidelines. They are not evidence based, nor do they take into consideration you as an individual. Would you go to a hairdresser to get your hair dyed, only to be informed that they only dye your hair blue at this salon, and thats your only option? NOOOOOO! You would not accept this and go elsewhere? 

Our maternity system is failing, and this is becoming more apparent. AIMS has submitted a response to the Health & Social Care Committee inquiry on the safety of maternity services in England. Clearly women are not getting what they want. Which we know is partially down to the awful system we have. I cant remember the last time I heard a women that was "high risk" but was also given ALL the information she needed to make an informed decision. However, the system would not be able to work in this manner if WOMEN did not accept it! 

We are being indoctrinated with horrifying birth stories of long labours, tearing, c sections and episiotomy. THEY ARE NOT NORMAL but we are being taught they are. Women pour out of hospitals believing the traumatic procedure they just endured was necessary and normal. Just look at whats happening now during covid! Women must learn about birth physiology to know that if you are healthy, a hospital birth is not conducive to a calm empowering experience. "Not allowed a home birth because of covid" NO WAY!! Do not take no for an answer, the more of you that comply, the more power they have for no beneficial outcome.   There are no laws that dictate you have to have a traumatic birth just because a doctor says you are "high risk". If you have been told this, do your own research! Usually you will find there is no evidence for what they are telling you anyway. 

If you believe birth is inherently dangerous, if you out of fear are complicit, you are passively propping up a system that does not need to be there. Yes we need medical intervention for a small number of women, yes some women are not able to make decisions for themselves for various reasons, but its up to the rest of us to take a stand and say NO!!! It is your body and your baby. Im not asking you to train to be a Doula or midwife, just to look at easily accessible research to make an informed decision. 

Luckily women are starting to wake up. They are starting to realise they answer to only themselves. So many educated, well informed women are turning to freebirth! This is wonderful. However as we are operating  in what appears to be a medical dictatorship, so many women are being reported to social services for having the birth they want! These are well educated women who have researched to make an informed decision. They dont feel they have the support from the NHS so are going it alone. I dont blame them! These poor women are now terrified that the social will get involved. To quote a mother from a freebirth site "  I find antenatal care really steals my peace and is fear based and not good for me even as someone they deem "low risk" 
That says everything really! 

Ladies we need a motherlution!! Luckily so many women are turning to unassisted birth. Many of you will say its dangerous, but luckily as there are so many now, we will soon see quantitive date to prove otherwise, I can assure you. 
Independent midwives need to be utilised, sadly there is no insurance for them at the moment due to bloody Covid!! There isnt even a reason, at this point the insurance companies are just saying in words in no particular order and hoping no one challenges their bullshit. 

Please share this if you agree and want to take control of your birth! If you are still crippled with fear about your birth, here is my advice to you. "You are a strong woman, you can do this, you are a birthing Goddess and someone that has a white coat, wears scrubs and has a machine that goes beep, does NOT make them more qualified than you to know whats right for you! Research, trust your body. If you find that you are genuinely unwell and fall into the small percentage of women that need help, this post is not about you. If you are healthy, take charge, own your birth and I promise you will not have a feeling like it". 

I will finish with an amazing quote from a dear friend a colleague. She is an experienced Midwife of 18 years. I could not agree with her statement more. (truncated)

WHAT THE HELL ?

It’s 3am on Sunday morning, and I can’t sleep because I can’t get these images out of my head.

I never thought I’d see the day in Australia where a women protesting peacefully, not blocking anyone, and holding up one protest sign criticising the policies of the government (saying exactly what hundreds of doctors are saying in Victoria)and another sign saying; ‘’Freedom of Speech’’ - ‘’ Human Rights’’ - ‘’Democracy’’ - and is assaulted by a police officer and forcibly has her protest signs taken from her. 

How can we ever criticise China again for launching brutal police assaults against Hong Kong residents protesting for Freedom of Speech, Democracy and Human Rights if Dan Andrews Police Force does this ?  

Dan Andrews must go. He has become power-drunk and lost all perspective. He has become singularity fixated on the number of infections irrespective of whether these people are even sick, and he is totally oblivious to the death and destruction his brutal lockdowns are causing. 

He is no longer capable of making rational balanced decisions, or simply evening considering if the costs of the lockdowns outweigh the benefits. 

This madness must end. I call on all good members of the Labor Party in the Victorian Parliament to urgently meet and remove him and appoint a new Premier. 

Andrews is not only destroying the state and taking the country down with it - he is destroying the Labor Party in Victoria as well. 

Please Labor MP’s in Victoria, you just can’t sit back and watch his happen - show some courage and act to remove this megalomaniac before it’s too late. 

Secondly, all state chief health officers should resign or be sacked. They have become star-struck by the TV cameras and think they are celebrities on some reality TV show.  

They to have lost perspective of the death, destruction, hardship and suffering the lockdowns and border closures they are recommending are causing. 

And they are not capable of admitting the tragic mistakes they have made, and reversing course.  It would be in the nations best interest to clean them all out and appoint new people that can come in with a fresh perspective and without the baggage of past decisions.

column36:
I read it a while ago and I found it quite interesting.

Anyone who thinks social distancing is a good idea for the next few years, or thinks a "benevolent" dictatorship is for the good of the people, good luck with that!

I am a free and sovereign human being and if you want to stay home, stay home. That is your sovereign right to choose.

If you want to wear a mask, wear a mask. That is your sovereign right to choose.

If you want to avoid big crowds, avoid big crowds. That is your sovereign right to choose.

I am not forced to fall into poverty for you. 
I am not obligated to abstain from human contact for you. 
I am not obligated to shop alone, without my friends and family, for you. 
I refuse to participate in the "quarantine life" until there is an unsafe and unproven vaccine that is distributed in eighteen months. 
I refuse to receive such a vaccine so that others feel safer. That IS my sovereign right to choose!!

If you are convinced that the vaccine is safe and effective, enjoy it.

Some of you are allowing fear and policies lacking scientifically accurate data to destroy our country and ruin our lives. I can't control your self-destructive behavior, but we all have a say in the country and the planet we live on. We need to tell legislators that we demand options.

 We have a constitutional right to take risks. Life is full of bacteria and viruses, many of which spread before symptoms appear and after they subside. We have the sovereign right to receive vaccines or to refuse them.
The data is inaccurate at best; purposely exaggerated to justify worst-case government abuses. Stop allowing the government to destroy:

- food supply
- small businesses
- medical autonomy
- access to primary care
- religious gatherings
- The right to privacy
- our mental health
- our freedom

When the "new normal" is filled with hunger, depression, suicide, child abuse, domestic violence, incarceration, government espionage, and sheer DESPERATION, the virus is going to seem preferable to the world you helped build.

Those who say that I (or anyone who supports the idea of reopening) am putting the economy above lives (as if the virus kills, but hunger does not) pay attention:

- You do not care about people killing themselves for lack of hope...
- You do not care about small businesses that will close their doors (their life) permanently
- You do not care about children, women and men who will be victims of domestic abuse.
- You do not care about people not being able to pay their mortgages and are evicted from their houses.
- You do not care about families not able to pay the bills because of their zero income right now.
- You don't care about people wondering where their next meal will come from.
- You don't care about people who will lose their sobriety and go back to addiction.
- You don't care about the people who will starve...
- You support the inevitable looting that will take place
- You do not care about anyone who has been killed the longer the lockdown lasts
- You don't care about people's mental health
- You do not care about children who do need teachers and references to guide and educate them.
- You don't mind the economy crashing around us.
- YOU REALLY DON'T CARE.

You love your shackles, begging your leaders for LONGER lockdowns and MORE regulations.

I will not tolerate someone else telling me that lives don't matter to me. 
I care about the whole situation. But you don't care about any of that, so...

YOU stay home.
YOU wear a mask.
YOU live in fear.

It is your choice to live as imposed on you. 
I have chosen to LIVE as a human being who has the right to decide.

column36: Australia is in really bad shape with the plandemic lock downs, they are not able to leave their homes for much of any reason. Flint Michigan cannot give their citizens clean water but they are rolling out facial recognition helmets for their police office...

Consider for a minute the irony of the protest at Melbourne’s Shrine of Remembrance today. A bunch of fed-up people gathering without a mask at a monument dedicated to the selfless men and women who fought for our nation’s freedom. 

Because they miss the pub. And can’t watch the footy. And can’t have a BBQ with ten friends. 

Cry me a fucking river. 

Now, I don’t want to generalise here, but I’m guessing this bunch might be a few sandwiches short of a picnic. Have a few roo’s loose in the top paddock. *Insert other derogatory quip here*. 

Why do I say that? Because this lockdown IS NOT THAT BAD. It isn’t. And this is coming from someone who lives in Victoria and has had her kids out of school since March and had a few full-blown melt downs in the past few weeks. 

It is difficult. It is painful in relation to what we are used to. It is weird and uncomfortable. And it’s ok to express that and feel that, but it’s NOT THAT BAD. Not fight with a gun for your country bad. Not live in a trench for months on end bad. Not see your best mate get blown to bits bad. 

I also miss my “freedom”. I miss seeing my kids with their mates. I miss going for a Sunday drive. I miss seeing my family. 

But I’m not about to break the rules that are there for all of us just to bitch about a shit couple of months. And it has been shit. Through the depths of winter after a pretty crap start to a new decade, I realise people are struggling. 

We are here because of a few people. Most of us have done the right thing and are paying the price for a few who think they are above everyone else.   

These special few believe they are fighting an “oppressive regime.”  Thats not what this is. Not by the Russia or North Korea standard anyway. It’s a local government that is scrambling for a way to stop people dying. If they really think there’s a ‘Dictator Dan’, they should take a trip to visit Kim Jong-un when this shit show is over.

Please realise that this is a short term period of pain for long-term gain. This is the only time in living memory we’ve all been asked to act as a group to help every single person in this state. 

Why did you pick this monument? The men and women who it honours are heroes. You are not. You’re just an ant in this mess like the rest of us. And now we are potentially facing a new Covid cluster because of the clusterfuck at our monument.

Get a grip. And put your fucking mask on so we can enjoy summer. 

THE END

Sick of lockdown? Buy a mask or some other shit to cheer you up. It won’t get you arrested and I guarantee it will make you smile. Something we all need right now.

column36:
ON THIS DAY: SASR Trooper Mark Donaldson - who is still a serving member of the ADF - exposed himself to enemy fire to protect injured Australian troops and then rescued an Afghan interpreter under heavy enemy fire during a contact on 2 September 2008 – actions for which he would be awarded the Victoria Cross for Australia. 
"In the early stages of the ambush," his citation reads, "Trooper Donaldson reacted spontaneously to regain the initiative. He moved rapidly between alternate positions of cover engaging the enemy with 66mm and 84mm anti-armour weapons as well as his M4 rifle. During an early stage of the enemy ambush, he deliberately exposed himself to enemy fire in order to draw attention to himself and thus away from wounded soldiers. This selfless act alone bought enough time for those wounded to be moved to relative safety."
Later, during the convoy's extraction, "a severely wounded coalition force interpreter was inadvertently left behind. Of his own volition and displaying complete disregard for his own safety, Trooper Donaldson moved alone, on foot, across approximately 80 metres of exposed ground to recover the wounded interpreter. His movement, once identified by the enemy, drew intense and accurate machine-gun fire from entrenched positions. Upon reaching the wounded coalition force interpreter, Trooper Donaldson picked him up and carried him back to the relative safety of the vehicles, then provided immediate first aid before returning to the fight."
We salute you, Mark. A true Aussie hero.

column36:
An ER Nurse posted this:

Anyone who can tell me what our end game is with the covid 19?
What is the magic formula that is going to allow us to sound the all clear?
Is it zero cases?
The only way that will happen is if we just stop testing and stop reporting.
Is it a vaccine?
It took 25 years for a chicken pox vaccine to be developed.
The smallpox inoculation was discovered in 1796 the last known natural case was in 1977.
We have a flu vaccine that is only 40 to 60% effective and less than half of the US population choose to get one, and roughly 20,000 Americans will die of the flu or flu complications.
Oh, you'll mandate it, like other vaccines are mandated in order to attend school, travel to some foreign countries, etc.
We already have a growing number people refusing well known vaccines that have been administered for decades but aren’t necessarily safe!
Do you really think people will flock to get a fast tracked, quickly tested vaccine, whose long term side effects and overall efficacy are anyone's best guess?
How long are we going to cancel and postpone and reconsider?
You aren't doing in person school until second quarter?
What if October's numbers are the same as August's?
You moved football to spring?
What if next March is worse than this one was?
When do we decide quality of life outweighs the risks?

Definition of cognitive 1 : of, relating to, being, or involving conscious intellectual activity (such as thinking, reasoning, or remembering) cognitive impairment 2 : based on or capable of being reduced to empirical factual knowledge Cognitive disorder Cognitive disorders (CDs), also known as neurocognitive disorders (NCDs), are a category of mental health disorders that primarily affect cognitive abilities including learning, memory, perception, and problem solving. Neurocognitive disorders include delirium and mild and major neurocognitive disorder (previously known as dementia). They are defined by deficits in cognitive ability that are acquired (as opposed to developmental), typically represent decline, and may have an underlying brain pathology[1]. The DSM-5 defines six key domains of cognitive function: executive function, learning and memory, perceptual-motor function, language, complex attention, and social cognition. Although Alzheimer's disease accounts for the majority of cases of neurocognitive disorders, there are various medical conditions that affect mental functions such as memory, thinking, and the ability to reason, including frontotemporal degeneration, Huntington’s disease, Lewy body disease, traumatic brain injury (TBI), Parkinson’s disease, prion disease, and dementia/neurocognitive issues due to HIV infection.[2] Neurocognitive disorders are diagnosed as mild and major based on the severity of their symptoms. While anxiety disorders, mood disorders, and psychotic disorders can also have an effect on cognitive and memory functions, the DSM-IV-TR does not consider these cognitive disorders, because loss of cognitive function is not the primary (causal) symptom.[3] Additionally, developmental disorders such as autism spectrum disorder are typically developed at birth or early in life as opposed to the acquired nature of neurocognitive disorders. Causes vary between the different types of disorders but most include damage to the memory portions of the brain.[4][5][6] Treatments depend on how the disorder is caused. Medication and therapies are the most common treatments; however, for some types of disorders such as certain types of amnesia, treatments can suppress the symptoms but there is currently no cure. Causes Delirium Delirium can be caused by the worsening of previous medical conditions, substance abuse or withdrawal, mental illness, severe pain, immobilization, sleep deprivation and hypnosis. column31: Sorry, it keeps sharing without my blurb! Infuriating!....... So, I have finally gotten around to writing another email to my little mans school, they are actually going to HATE me! 😂😂 I will be "that parent" that they dread opening emails from! 😂😂 I haven't sent it yet, so if there is anything you think I've missed or any excellent studies I haven't included, let me know asap! Dear Mrs **************** I hope you are well and have enjoyed the school holidays? I thought I would write this email in anticipation of **** starting school in a couple of weeks time, now that schools have received the updated guidance from the government. As you are aware, our concerns are (and have always been) about the welfare of the children relating to the effects that any of these measures are likely to have on their mental and physical health, rather than the risks from any virus. The evidence still indicates that children are at phenomenally low risk of both contracting the illness and/or spreading it. I am pleased to see that the measures your school have put into place do not seem to be particularly extreme and are still very focused on promoting a fun and sociable early years education environment. There are however, a few things that I wish to discuss with you in more detail. * Hand sanitiser- I was wondering if any risk assessments have been done regarding the frequent use of these products, especially long term use of them by children? I have included a list below of the most commonly used ingredients and wondered if the school was aware of this information? 1. Parabens (methylparaben, butylparaben, propylparaben, etc.) preserve other ingredients and extend shelf life, but can have hormone-disrupting effects. Parabens can cause diminished muscle mass and extra fat storing, and topical parabens have been detected in human breast tumors. 2. Ureas are a primary cause of contact dermatitis. They can release formaldehyde and cause joint pain, heart irregularities, and a weakened immune system. 3. Synthetic colours (shown on labels as FD&C or D&C, followed by a colour and a number) are made from coal tar and contain heavy metal salts that may deposit toxins onto the skin. This causes skin sensitivity and irritation. Animal studies have shown almost all synthetic colours to be carcinogenic. 4. Diethanolamine (DEA) is linked to cancer, developmental/reproductive toxicity, allergies/immunotoxicity, and organ system toxicity. 5. Propylene Glycol (also Propylene Oxide and Polyethylene Glycol) is on the FDA’s website as a known carcinogen. It weakens skin cells and is linked to developmental/reproductive toxicity, allergies/immunotoxicity, and organ system toxicity. 6. Synthetic fragrances often contain phthalates, which are endocrine disruptors that mimic hormones and may alter genital development. 7. 1,4-Dioxane may not be listed on ingredient labels, as it’s considered a “contaminant” or “by-product” of the ethoxylation process rather than an ingredient. However, this chemical is known to cause cancer, so for safety reasons its best to avoid ethoxylation ingredients, including those ending in “eth” (myreth, oleth, laureth, ceteareth, etc.), and those with PEG, polyethylene, polyethylene glycol, polyoxyethylene, or oxynol in their names. 8. Ethyl Alcohol (ethanol) is linked to cancer, birth defects, developmental/reproductive toxicity, and organ system toxicity. 9. Benzalkonium Chloride (BAC) belongs to a group of germicides known as “quats” and is linked to cancer, allergies/immunotoxicity, and organ system toxicity. 10. Sodium Lauryl Sulfate or Sodium Laureth Sulfate is linked to skin and eye irritation, as well as organ toxicity, developmental/reproductive toxicity, neurotoxicity, endocrine disruption, Eco toxicological and biochemical or cellular changes, possible mutations, and cancer. It can also damage cell membranes and possibly cause hair loss. This list is not exhaustive, I'm quite sure there are other ingredients with equally concerning potential side effects which are worth considering before encouraging the children to use them regularly. There are also other concerns relating to the use of sanitisers and excessive cleaning, including inadvertently increasing the prevalence of “super bugs” and also the widely studied effects on the skin and gut microbiome. It has been proven in many studies that people, and especially children, need germs (both “good” and “bad”), in order to develop a healthy immune system. These same studies have shown time and time again, that children raised in an environment that was too sterile were actually far more prone to illness and less healthy than their peers who had been raised in a different, less clinical environment. Those who were not allowed to get dirty and were shielded more from germs had many more issues associated with gut problems, eczema, asthma, allergies, etc, etc. Given the current climate of fear relating to (truncated)

column36:
Here is a list, in no particular order, of the problems with Zoe Lee's arrest.

1. She probably did not commit the crime of incitement. It requires first, intent, and second, for the crime incited to have actually happened. (See Crimes Act 1958 (Vic) s 321G). She was probably falsely arrested.

2. Daniel Andrews claimed, when questioned the following day (today), that he had not seen the video. This is either a lie, or he specifically told his staff not to show it to him so that he could say he had not seen it.

3. The Assistant Police Commissioner (APC) distinguished her event from BLM because hers was during stage 4 lockdown, and BLM was during stage 3. Wilfully deceptive. Ballarat - the location of Zoe's event - is in stage 3 lockdown.

4. The APC distinguished her event from BLM on the basis that BLM encouraged social distancing and mask wearing. So did her event, very specifically... I quote, "All social distancing measures are to be followed so we don't get arrested please. Please wear a mask unless you have a medical reason not to." Again, wilfully deceptive.

5. The APC said, “While this deadly virus doesn’t discriminate, we won’t discriminate and we can’t discriminate, in holding people to account.” - err, Black Lives Matter, anyone??? This made me snort my coffee out my nose. VicPol are not enforcing a righteous standard, but a political one. Agree with their politics, they lie to defend you. Disagree, they lie to falsely arrest you.

6. The police simply do not have to handcuff a person, do not have to arrest a person, and do not have to execute a search warrant under these circumstances. Doing do is unusual on all three counts. The doing of all three, in front of her family, whilst pregnant and compliant, is nothing short of intimidation tactics. (Not to mention she committed no crime, see point 1).

7. From her interview the following day: "Sorry about my bimbo moment, but I didn’t realise I wasn’t allowed to. I wanted to protest in Melbourne but obviously realised I wasn’t allowed to do that… so I just wanted to feel like I was doing something, you know standing up for human rights, and you know I am just a passionate person and I am sick of the lockdowns, I am sick of hearing about suicides, I personally lost my job, and I am just sick of watching the economy collapse. It got to the point where I just wanted to peacefully protest." Okay, so she is not some sort of anti-lockdown fanatic, or serial protester, or any such thing... and she intended no harm. This accords with the phrasing of her event - among other words, she said, "Here in Ballarat we can be a voice for those in stage 4 lockdowns."

8. Despite point 7, above, the APC implied very heavily in his press conference that she probably had a history of negative police interactions which led to her handcuffing. Rather unfair conjecture.

9. Even if she did seem to breach the Crimes Act, the Act is not allowed to be applied in a way that infringes on her freedom to politically communicate. This is a well known constitutional law doctrine in Australia, and state law is limited on this basis.

10. Even if she did seem to breach the Crimes Act, she has a further protection. The Victorian Police are not allowed to carry out their duties in a manner that breaches the Victorian Charter of Human Rights and Responsibilities which includes the rights to "peaceful assembly and freedom of association" and "freedom of expression"

11. The APC called it “That serious offence of inciting a protest” - actually, what she did (well, didn't do - see point 1) is the most utterly benign, low level crimes. Their actions were outrageously disproportionate.

12. The arresting officers later told Zoe they didn't want to do it. If this is true, then it's as I suspected - politicised leaders in the police force (a change of government usually changes that - hint, hint Victoria).

Summary: Andrews lied, the Assistant Police Commissioner lied, the media didn't bother holding them to account. The bored, Facebook-surfing police went digging to find an offence which they could use to "teach her a lesson" based on the fact they disagreed with her politics... and misread the offence, or hoped nobody would read it, thereby booking her for something she did not do, in handcuffs, in front of her children, and made off with her devices and searched her home.

This is the latest in a long line of incidents of VicPol persecuting those with political differences. See my earlier posts.

Somebody wake me up already. I don't like this dream.

column36:
THE OPEN LETTER FROM DOCTORS TO PREMIER DANIEL ANDREWS 

Dear Premier,
We, the undersigned, are senior medical practitioners of various specialities who practice in Victoria and are deeply concerned with the Victorian government’s management of the SARS-CoV-2 (COVID-19) viral pandemic as a public health issue.
The purpose of this letter is to make you aware that not all medical practitioners are in agreement with the Chief Medical Officer and the Victorian government regarding the most effective way to control this disease. We believe that an alternative medical response is required that reflects what we know about the spread of the virus, those who have died from it, and the impact that the stage 3-4 lockdown restrictions are having on the physical and mental health of the general population.
For the sake of people in Victoria with other medical illnesses, it is vital that Stage 4 restrictions be lifted on schedule in mid-September.
This letter details our concerns and recommendations. We are ready to offer any assistance we can to help create and implement a revised, effective and just response to the Victorian situation; to this end we would be pleased to meet with you at your convenience to discuss the matter further.
Government Response to Covid-19 and Available Data
Focusing on the numbers of cases of COVID-19 is at best an unsophisticated way of looking at disease management. Factors such as the side effects of any policy, its cost effectiveness, the quality of life years lost, and the cost per life saved are fundamental when considering disease management. In addition, any policy to manage any disease must be reviewed in light of new data.
We believe that the government’s initial response to handling COVID-19, via a stage 3 lockdown to ‘flatten the curve’, was reasonable in view of the limited information available at the time on the outbreak in China and the alarming number of deaths in Italy. The initial response, though arguably excessive, was still highly effective in preserving medical capacity and allowing time to co-ordinate a full medical response, with the community accepting that the social and economic consequences were reasonable and for the common good.
However, we now know that whilst COVID-19 is highly contagious, it is of limited virulence.
Whilst an accurate cause of death of a person can be difficult to determine, we are told that since March 2020, 565 Victorian patients have died either with or from the virus (31st August numbers). This compares with annual Victorian deaths of approximately 10,000 patients with cardiovascular disease and 11,000 with cancer. Accordingly, the COVID-19 deaths are a relatively small proportion of the 114 deaths per day that are normally seen in Victoria. In comparison, since the start of March COVID-19 has been associated with 3 of the 114 deaths per day.
Most of the 565 deaths have occurred in nursing homes which according to doctors currently working in this environment have described causal factors related not only to the virus but to other care related issues, including isolation, loneliness, and related diminished nutritional intake.
However, in Victoria we have had 541 LESS deaths this July compared to July last year. (3,561 deaths compared to 4,102 deaths in July 2019).
In Australia last year, 2019, in the month of July alone we had 71,000 new laboratory confirmed cases, and a total of 313,000 laboratory confirmed cases of influenza for the year. This is only a fraction of the actual total cases of influenza, as many cases go untested.
In August 2017 we had 99,000 new laboratory confirmed cases of Influenza and a total of over 250,000 cases for the year.
During 2017 and 2019 Influenza resulted in 25-30,000 hospital admissions and up to 2500 ICU admissions across Australia. Three per cent of hospital admissions were pregnant women and up to 18 per cent were under the age of 16.
The deaths from Influenza each and every year is between 3500 and 4000, according to the Australian Influenza Specialist Interest Group website and the Australian Bureau of Statistics. This is despite recent excellent rates of vaccination in the vulnerable population and millions of vaccinations utilised each year. (2020,18 million, 2019 13.2 million, 2018 11 million, 2016 8.3 million)
The vast majority of deaths associated with COVID-19 have occurred in frail people over 80 years, many of whom also had significant co-morbidities. In Victoria more than 73 per cent of known COVID-19 deaths resided in nursing homes. (381 out of 524 and 30 out of 52 in NSW, as of August 30).
For people who are physically well and under 60 years of age, the mortality risk is extremely low. Contrary to what you have said, Mr Andrews, the virus DOES discriminate. See graphs below.
Since June 2020, the death rate has risen sharply in aged care facilities where the risk of transmission of COVID-19 has been unacceptably high. However, the government, and the doctors advising (truncated)

column31: Please feel free to Copy and Paste LETTER WRITTEN FOR A PARENT TO SEND TO HER SON'S SCHOOL ABOUT TEMPERATURE TESTING Dear [names], Re: Temperature testing my son I am writing to you in regards to your coronavirus protocols when my son, [name], returns to school in September. I understand that you may be subjecting him and the other pupils to regular temperature checks. I would like to register in writing that I do not consent to [name] receiving temperature checks of his forehead, and only give consent to his temperature being checked at the wrist. This is because, having consulted with medical professionals, it is clear to me that repeated temperature testing at the forehead with an infrared ray has never been shown to be safe, and could cause significant harms, especially to a developing child. When one aims an infrared ray at the forehead, one directly targets the pineal gland. In case you were not aware, the pineal gland is a small, pine-cone shaped gland of the endocrine system, a structure of the diencephalon of the brain. It produces the hormone melatonin, which influences sexual development and sleep/wake cycles. The pineal gland connects the endocrine system with the nervous system, and it converts nerve signals from the sympathetic system of the peripheral nervous system into hormone signals. The pineal gland is involved in several functions of the body, including the secretion of hormones, regulation of endocrine functions, and converting nervous system signals to endocrine signals. It causes sleepiness, and influences sexual development, immune system development, and antioxidant activity In light of these facts, aiming an infrared gun at this vital brain structure, at a critical time of a child's development, raises many important questions regarding safety and short and long-term effects. As there is no compelling evidence to show that infrared rays do not damage the pineal gland, and as temperature checking is in any case more accurate at the wrist than the forehead, I only consent to my son being temperature checked at the wrist. I have advised him that he has my permission to firmly refuse if the school attempts to temperature test his forehead. I am also attaching to this letter a statement from my son, stating that he does not consent to being temperature checked at the forehead. [Name] is Gillick competent and understands the issues involved, so if a forehead temperature check is conducted on him, it will have been under duress and therefore unlawful. In light of the information I have provided you with in this letter, I would also like you to consider abandoning forehead temperature testing entirely, and instead, conducting wrist-only testing on all pupils, as this is safer, more effective, and less alarming for pupils than having a gun aimed at their heads, the connotations of which can be highly unnerving for some. Please respond to this letter at your earliest possible convenience acknowledging my revoking of consent for forehead temperature testing for my son. Yours sincerely, [Name] STATEMENT FROM [MY SON] I, [name], would like to state formally and for the record that I do not consent to being temperature checked at the forehead. I understand the issues involved and understand this procedure is not known to be safe, and that testing at the wrist is both safer and more effective. I understand that if the school pressurises me into being temperature checked at the forehead against my wishes, it will have been under duress, and therefore unlawful. Signed *_____________* Dated: *________*

column36:
Breaking News, Newport Beach, CA:  Physicians for Informed Consent Publishes New Educational Document on Risk of Aluminum in Vaccines 

Physicians for Informed Consent (PIC), an educational nonprofit organization focused on science and statistics, has just released its Aluminum Vaccine Risk Statement (VRS) entitled “Aluminum in Vaccines: What Parents Need to Know.” The educational document answers important questions about the risks of aluminum-containing vaccines administered to newborns, infants and children.

“The COVID-19 pandemic has shown us that the public is very interested in weighing the risks of infectious diseases versus the risks of vaccines,” said Dr. Shira Miller, PIC founder and president. “Parents and the public must become knowledgeable about aluminum in vaccines because even though it is used as an adjuvant in many vaccines, it is a neurotoxin—and overexposure may lead to significant harm, including problems in motor, sensory, and cognitive function.” Currently, up to 22 doses of aluminum-containing vaccines are recommended to children, with 11 doses recommended from birth to 6 months of age.

The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) and the Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry (ATSDR), agencies of the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (HHS), have raised concerns about the negative effects of aluminum exposure in humans. In scientific studies, small amounts of aluminum that remain in the body have been observed to interfere with a variety of cellular and metabolic processes in the nervous system and in tissues of other parts of the body. Some of the most damaging effects of aluminum range from motor skill impairment to encephalopathy (altered mental state, personality changes, difficulty thinking, loss of memory, seizures, coma, and more). 

The FDA states that if some vaccines did not include aluminum (i.e., aluminum hydroxide and aluminum phosphate) as an adjuvant, the immune response they trigger may be diminished. Therefore, aluminum is included in many vaccines on the childhood schedule, including the following: hepatitis B (HepB), Haemophilus influenzae type b (PedvaxHIB), pneumococcal (PCV), hepatitis A (HepA), human papillomavirus (HPV), meningococcal B (MenB), and diphtheria, tetanus, and pertussis (DTaP and Tdap). 

“Vaccines are administered preventively to healthy people, not people with acute or chronic infections, so it’s crucially important to know the safety data upon which one’s recommendations are based,” said Dr. Miller. “PIC developed the Aluminum VRS to help families and their physicians advance their understanding of the risks of aluminum adjuvants, so they may engage in informed decision-making.” 

Parents and caregivers are encouraged to discuss the Aluminum VRS educational documents with their children’s doctor. To read the Aluminum VRS or to download it, please visit http://physiciansforinformedconsent.org/aluminum.

column31: Hi everyone! Writing this post as I am desperate to find a solution to help my son. He is 5 and constantly ill. Every 2-3 weeks high temp, very often 40C, which can last for a week ( just fluctuates between 39 - 40), always enlarged lymph nodes on the left side of his neck, his splin has also been enlarged for the past 3 years. He gets recurrent tonsillitis and since April been on antibiotics 7 times 😭. Also since April he is constantly complaining of stomach aches, now every day for the past month and joint pains, especially in his knees. He has lost 1.5 kg of his weight, and is underweight for his age. He wakes up with stomachache ( hunger aches?), complains of it throughout a day ( after food as well), eats small portions, but more frequently than normal. He is no longer active like he used to be, doesn't want to ride his bike ( due to pains ) for example, can't walk in shops or around the block ( mummy my legs are hurting, I can't walk). He was diagnosed with duodenitis last year, but no medication was ever prescribed. We have been to Peds several times, and they are just brushing us off, his bloods were in the range of normal, few times in the middle of tonsillitis his CRP marker was raised to 50 to suggest inflammation. But got down to normal range after antibiotics. We have seen private ENT doctor, who is suggesting tonsillectomy, as he has enlarged adenoids and glands. He is on a healthy diet, probiotics, herbal teas to support immunity, vit C, kefir, other vitamins. He was ill throughout winter, and was off school completely since April -we were isolating,due to his illnesses not seing anyone for nearly whole summer. I suspect that due to recurrent tonsillitis, antibiotics, strep and staph infections, his gut flora is damaged ( probiotics are not helping, possibly his duodenitis may have turned into gastroduodenitis ( Peds are not willing to investigate any further), his joint pains are potentially a complication he developed (juvenile arthritis? may be not related?) Has anyone got any advice? Anyone in Devon area, who can suggest a good Homeopath? Sorry for the long post, but I don't know what else to do to help my son out. Thank you for any input!

(Jabin Botsford/The Washington Post)
column36:
“One of President Trump’s top medical advisers is urging the White House to embrace a controversial “herd immunity” strategy to combat the pandemic, which would entail allowing the coronavirus to spread through most of the population to quickly build resistance to the virus, while taking steps to protect those in nursing homes and other vulnerable populations, according to five people familiar with the discussions.”

“The approach’s chief proponent is Scott Atlas, a neuroradiologist and fellow at Stanford’s conservative Hoover Institution, who joined the White House in August as a pandemic adviser. He has advocated that the United States adopt the model Sweden has used to respond to the virus outbreak according to these officials, which relies on lifting restrictions so healthy people can build immunity to the disease rather than limiting social and business interactions to prevent the virus from spreading.”

“Sweden’s handling of the pandemic has been heavily criticized by public health officials and infectious-disease experts as reckless — the country’s infection and death rates are among the world’s highest. It also hasn’t escaped the deep economic problems resulting from the pandemic.”

“But Sweden’s approach has gained support among some conservatives who argue that social distancing restrictions are crushing the economy and infringing on people’s liberties.”

The White House denies that this policy is being discussed, but Atlas has clashed with Dr. Fauci and Dr. Birx on their response of the pandemic. 

Atlas argues that an increase in cases will move the nation to herd immunity and won’t lead to an increase in deaths if the vulnerable are protected. 

Do you agree with President Trump’s new medical adviser?

Should the United States have adopted Sweden’s approach all along and let virus run its course while focusing  protective efforts on our most vulnerable?

#OpenOhioAllTheWay
#GoodIdeasDoNotRequireForce
#EndMedicalTyrannyNow

column36:
THIS MADNESS MUST END 

Victorian Doctors write to their Premier 

Dear Premier,

We, the undersigned, are senior medical practitioners of various specialities who practice in Victoria and are deeply concerned with the Victorian government’s management of the SARS-CoV-2 (COVID-19) viral pandemic as a public health issue.

The purpose of this letter is to make you aware that not all medical practitioners are in agreement with the Chief Medical Officer and the Victorian government regarding the most effective way to control this disease. 

We believe that an alternative medical response is required that reflects what we know about the spread of the virus, those who have died from it, and the impact that the stage 3-4 lockdown restrictions are having on the physical and mental health of the general population.

For the sake of people in Victoria with other medical illnesses, it is vital that Stage 4 restrictions be lifted on schedule in mid-September.

This letter details our concerns and recommendations. We are ready to offer any assistance we can to help create and implement a revised, effective and just response to the Victorian situation; to this end we would be pleased to meet with you at your convenience to discuss the matter further.  

Focusing on the numbers of cases of COVID-19 is at best an unsophisticated way of looking at disease management. Factors such as the side effects of any policy, its cost effectiveness, the quality of life years lost, and the cost per life saved are fundamental when considering disease management. In addition, any policy to manage any disease must be reviewed in light of new data.

We believe that the government’s initial response to handling COVID-19, via a stage 3 lockdown to ‘flatten the curve’, was reasonable in view of the limited information available at the time on the outbreak in China and the alarming number of deaths in Italy. 

The initial response, though arguably excessive, was still highly effective in preserving medical capacity and allowing time to co-ordinate a full medical response, with the community accepting that the social and economic consequences were reasonable and for the common good.

However, we now know that whilst COVID-19 is highly contagious, it is of limited virulence.

Whilst an accurate cause of death of a person can be difficult to determine, we are told that since March 2020, 565 Victorian patients have died either with or from the virus (31st August numbers). 

This compares with annual Victorian deaths of approximately 10,000 patients with cardiovascular disease and 11,000 with cancer. Accordingly, the COVID-19 deaths are a relatively small proportion of the 114 deaths per day that are normally seen in Victoria. In comparison, since the start of March COVID-19 has been associated with 3 of the 114 deaths per day.

Most of the 565 deaths have occurred in nursing homes which according to doctors currently working in this environment have described causal factors related not only to the virus but to other care related issues, including isolation, loneliness, and related diminished nutritional intake.

However, in Victoria we have had 541 LESS deaths this July compared to July last year. (3,561 deaths compared to 4,102 deaths in July 2019).

In Australia last year, 2019, in the month of July alone we had 71,000 new laboratory confirmed cases, and a total of 313,000 laboratory confirmed cases of influenza for the year. This is only a fraction of the actual total cases of influenza, as many cases go untested.

In August 2017 we had 99,000 new laboratory confirmed cases of Influenza and a total of over 250,000 cases for the year.

During 2017 and 2019 Influenza resulted in 25-30,000 hospital admissions and up to 2500 ICU admissions across Australia. Three per cent of hospital admissions were pregnant women and up to 18 per cent were under the age of 16.

The deaths from Influenza each and every year is between 3500 and 4000, according to the Australian Influenza Specialist Interest Group website and the Australian Bureau of Statistics. This is despite recent excellent rates of vaccination in the vulnerable population and millions of vaccinations utilised each year. (2020,18 million, 2019 13.2 million, 2018 11 million, 2016 8.3 million)

The vast majority of deaths associated with COVID-19 have occurred in frail people over 80 years, many of whom also had significant co-morbidities. In Victoria more than 73 per cent of known COVID-19 deaths resided in nursing homes. (381 out of 524 and 30 out of 52 in NSW, as of August 30).

For people who are physically well and under 60 years of age, the mortality risk is extremely low. Contrary to what you have said, Mr Andrews, the virus DOES discriminate. See graphs below.

Since June 2020, the death rate has risen sharply in aged care facilities where the risk of transmission of COVID-19 has been unacceptably high. However, the government, and the doctors advising it, have not (truncated)

(Herald Sun)
Senior doctors across Melbourne are urging politicians not to support a state of emergency extension, saying the move threatens to “destroy” the health and wellbeing of fed-up Victorians.

In a letter to Premier Daniel Andrews, seen by NCA NewsWire, 13 medical practitioners outlined their concerns about the State Government’s response to the COVID-19 pandemic.

They say it is “vital” stage four restrictions are lifted on September 13, believe “an alternative medical response” is required and highlight key data they think is being “excluded”.

During question time in parliament on Tuesday afternoon Opposition Upper House leader David Davis demanded the Premier and Health Minister Jenny Mikakos meet the doctors who penned the letter.

“I ask that the Minister for Health with the Premier meet with all 13 doctors to listen to their views,” he said.

In the letter the doctors wrote: “It is our professional opinion that the stage 4 lockdown policy has caused unprecedented negative economic and social outcomes in people, which in themselves are having negative health outcomes.”

Speaking to NCA NewsWire, Box Hill Hospital urologist Dr Geoff Wells said he hoped the letter would convince the government to lift harsh stage four restrictions on September 13.

“When I see my patients and ask them how they’re coping, the number one response is the sadness at not being able to see their grandchildren for three, four or five months and the ones who live on their own are extremely isolated,” he said.

“The mood of the population has changed dramatically in the past two weeks – there seems to be one half that is getting angrier and angrier and the other half which has just lost all hope – these policies are effecting the general psyche of the community.

“We just want to have significant input into this response instead of a blanket approach that is harming the general population.”

The letter – a combined effort from urologists, psychiatrists and surgeons – sent to the Premier’s office on Monday compared coronavirus data with other serious medical concerns.

Well-known Royal Melbourne Hospital transplant surgeon Dr Bob Millar, Monash Hospital orthopaedic surgeon Dr Jon Bare and Nossell Institute for Global Health public health physician Nathan Grills were among the contributors.

Professors John Murtagh, Haydn Walters and Kuruvilla George, Dr Peter Denton, Dr William Edwards, Dr Andrew Taylor, Dr Michael Knight, Dr John Mathai and Dr Eamonn Mathieson also had their say.

For the past week a new CoVID-19 conspiracy has been making the rounds on social media. Using a document published by the Australian Bureau of Statistics that is intended to provide guidance to doctors, the claim is that doctors are carelessly and baselessly attributing deaths to CoVID-19 in an attempt to inflate the mortality rate. It’s a disingenuous attempt by laypeople who have no knowledge of how to write, or have ever written a death certificate, to further cast doubt on this pandemic by using ‘official documentation’ which is not intended for layperson use.

The use of these selectively chosen screen-shot ‘official documents’ is done to misinform those who see it, cause a loss of faith in the health system by planting seeds of doubt, and ultimately intend to continue propagating a false narrative regarding CoVID-19. 

This tactic is not old. Such misinformation has been spread to cast doubt on the mortality rate in Europe and the United States. Usually, the supporting evidence for these claims is pure heresay: someone knew ‘someone’ who was falsely certified as a CoVID-related death, but when you ask for evidence to verify the claim it never ever comes.

For those who have been hoodwinked by these ‘truth-seekers’ peddling this latest conspiracy, let me explain something. A death certificate is a legal document and every doctor has a responsibility to certify death accurately and based on the evidence and the clinical picture that is presented to them.

Every doctor is trained to, and understands how a death certificate is supposed to be filled. 

1. There is the DIRECT cause of death 
2. There are the antecedents that CONTRIBUTED directly to the direct cause of death
3. There are other significant underlying co-morbid conditions that contributed to the final outcome.

CoVID-19 is not listed as the  direct cause of death. What’s listed as the direct cause of death is the respiratory failure, stroke, multi-organ failure, cardiac arrest etc that CoVID contributed to. CoVID would only be listed as an antecedent that contributed to the final outcome. 

Sometimes, in settings where deterioration is quick and there is no capacity for testing, certain things can be assumed based on the clinical picture. For example, if an otherwise well aged care resident suddenly develops symptoms of secondary pneumonia and respiratory distress in an aged care setting where half of the residents have influenza, and dies before you’ve had the opportunity to swab them, then the contributing antecedent can in that case be assumed to be influenza, because if it quacks like a duck and waddles like a duck, then it’s likely a duck. 

That ‘reasonable assumption’ that influenza was an antecedent could probably be confirmed with testing, but swabbing dead patients and prolonging the suffering of loved ones who are waiting for a death certificate to be filled in order to organise funerals, is unnecessary and cruel. Because at the end of the day the DIRECT cause of death is going to be listed as pneumonia or acute respiratory failure, not influenza. 

If we ever have any doubt about the cause of death, we cannot fill out a death certificate and we refer the patient to the coroner. 

Simply put: doctors are not inflating CoVID-19 mortality rates. If anything, the COVID-19 related death rate is likely being UNDER-REPORTED. Statistical data comparing death rates during March and April with death data averages from previous years in several countries showed the following trends:

- In March, France recorded 15,433 additional deaths which were unexplained by the official COVID-19 statistics.

- In March, Italy recorded 24,091 additional deaths which are were not explained by the official COVID-19 statistics.

- In March, Spain recorded 10,151 additional deaths which are were not explained by the official COVID-19 statistics.

- In Britain, there were an extra 12,197 deaths in April, over and above those officially registered as COVID-19 deaths.

- In New York City, where the deadliest  outbreak in the US occurred, there were 3,799 excess deaths recorded in April above those officially registered as COVID-19 deaths. 

Furthermore, during the height of the pandemic in the original epicentre of COVID-19, independent researchers monitoring Wuhan’s crematoriums reported findings that likely contradict the official death rate. In January, Wuhan’s 8 crematoriums, which traditionally operate in the morning in keeping with Chinese funerary traditions, were functioning 24 hours a day, operating at 6 times their strictly regulated rate.  Estimating that the usual funeral figure for a city of nine million people would be about 136 a day, escalation of crematorium operations by up to six times would have enabled about 816 daily cremations. Based on this level of cremation, the ‘official’ death toll of 4634 would have been reached in just 6 days. 

As I said: deaths are likely under-reported, especially (truncated)

I don't want to contribute to the new abnormal either....but it's a small private school and I am good friends with the staff. Unsure of what to do if/when he gets a fever!

column1: Arnica - Parents' Support Network, Promoting Natural Immunity
column31: Hi all my son was in the ICU unit last year with a bad reaction to croup which cause serious breathing difficulties. He is pretty much non verbal and he is 21 months old. I just had a thought, immunization was discussed with the dr and he he didnt seem happy. I explained that I had made an informed decision. I slept at the hospital and tried to be with him as much as possible but do you think maybe they immunised him without my permission?

column1: Arnica - Parents' Support Network, Promoting Natural Immunity
column31: Hi, I am hoping to get some advice for my 7 year old son. He has recently started gagging. More so in mornings than evenings. (Even before breakfast) I rang the doctor and she seems to think it could possibly be indigestion. So doctor has prescribed omeprazole. I’m not too keen on giving him the meds unless absolutely necessary. We have changed our diet plan slightly over the last week or so. So he’s not eating after 6pm and cut down on his snacking. It hasn’t made much difference to be honest. I’m worried it’ll affect him in school, As I’ve noticed he struggles to read out loud without gagging. He had his online language lesson earlier and the teacher asked him to read couple of sentences, he struggling to read as he was gagging in between. Any other tips? Thanks in advance

column1: Arnica - Parents' Support Network, Promoting Natural Immunity
column31: Hi there, I’m looking for recommendations for resizable baby wipes. Cheeky Wipes seem to be the most popular. If anyone has done there own, what oil have you used to keep them fresh? Thanks 🙏🏻
